notes_display: Battle of Cartagena.  This piece is identical to the medal referenced, except for two minute differences on the reverse; the title given to Ogle, "ADML", not "GENL", and the month in the exergue being "AP," not "APL".  Referenced medal is closest match.
issue_obverse_figure_description_s: Full length figure of Vernon facing left.  A Cannon on the  left and an an anchor on the right.
issue_obverse_legend_s: THE . BRITISH : GLORY . REVIV . D . BY . ADMIRAL : VERNON [N's reversed]
issue_reverse_figure_description_s: Large fort at right; seven ships approching town of Carthagena with two small vessels within its harbor.
issue_reverse_legend_s: AD . VERNON : ADML , OGLE . TOOK . CARTHAGENA . BY . SEA . AND . LAND . | AP . 1 . 174 : 1
